Document Title: Platform Incident Report – Aluva Station
Date: 14 September 2025
Prepared By: Station Controller (Evening Shift)

At 18:22 hrs, while Trainset KM12 was boarding passengers at Aluva Station, a male passenger approximately 35 years old slipped on the tactile strip near Car 2 entry point. Weather conditions included heavy rainfall earlier in the day, leaving parts of the platform damp despite cleaning.

Immediate Response:

- Train Operator activated the emergency brake, halting the train within 3 seconds.

- Security staff responded within 1 minute, escorting the injured passenger to the first-aid room.

- First aid administered (cleaning and bandaging minor abrasions on knee and forearm). Passenger remained conscious and alert.

- Passenger referred to Ernakulam General Hospital for further medical check-up, accompanied by security.

Service Impact:

- Delay of 7 minutes on KM12 departure.

- Announcements made over PA system citing “operational delay” to passengers.

- Downstream trains rescheduled with minor adjustments.

Investigation Notes:

- CCTV Camera AL-05 footage reviewed and archived.

- Root cause linked to overcrowding during evening peak, wet flooring, and rushing behavior by passenger.

- Incident logged in Emergency Register (Entry No. INC-2785).

Recommendations:

- Additional caution announcements during rain.

- Increased cleaning frequency of tactile strips.

- Station staff to guide boarding passengers more actively during peak hours.

- Safety bulletin to be issued to all controllers by 16 September 2025.